    "crs123": {
        "title": "Interaction Design for Online Video and Television",
        "abstract": "This course features: \\ - An up-to-date overview of online video and TV applications  \\ - A framework describing the different aspects of such applications \\ - Interaction Design principles for TV and online video applications \\ - User testing tips and heuristics to evaluate these applications \\ - A plenary exercise applying the design principles and heuristics \\ - Future outlook on television and online video \\  \\ The course builds on the successful CHI2012 course â€œSocial Interaction Design for Online Video and Televisionâ€. It has been expanded and extensively updated including the most recent evolutions in this fast moving field, and taking into account comments and suggestions from previous attendees. It also draws on previous courses by the instructors at other conferences. \\  \\ The presentation will be a lecture format with plenty of examples and videos, including exercises and plenary discussions. \\  \\ Instructorsâ€™ background \\ David Geerts has a PhD in Social Sciences at the KU Leuven, Belgium where he is Research Manager of the Centre for User Experience Research. David is specialized in user-centered design and evaluation of social TV. He has organized several workshops, SIGs and tutorials at various conferences. \\  \\ Pablo Cesar has a PhD from Helsinki University of Technology. He is a senior researcher at CWI (The National Research Institute for Mathematics and Computer Science), in the Netherlands. He has (co)authored over 50 conference papers and journal articles about multimedia systems and infrastructures, social media sharing, interactive media, multimedia content modelling, and user interaction.",
