    "pn2020": {
        "title": "DoDo Game, a Color Vision Deficiency Screening Test for Young children",
        "abstract": "This paper presents â€œDoDoâ€™s Catching Adventure,â€ a new color vision deficient screening test for young children. Early detection of color blindness among children is useful for parents and teachers to better understand childrenâ€™s needs, to overcome difficulties in learning, and for life and career planning. Unfortunately, current color screening tests are not designed for young children; most require more advanced verbal or cognitive skills. DoDo game has taken a new approach by embedding game elements into a color vision screening test. A user study conducted at Singapore National Eye Centre on twenty-eight children, identified fourteen as Red-Green deficient subjects as did by Ishihara screening test, showed that DoDo was adequately effective in identifying Red-Green color vision deficiency and comparable to two current gold standard colorblind tests, Ishihara and D15.",
